-- 
BHF Chief Says Bank Attracted New Money, Handelsblatt Reports

-- B y   A a r o n   K i r c h f e l d
-- 
2011-05-08T15:00:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/bhf-chief-says-bank-attracted-new-money-handelsblatt-reports.html
BHF-Bank AG, the German private bank
owned by  Deutsche Bank AG (DBK) , has attracted 500 million euros ($720
million) in new money from wealthy clients so far this year,
 Handelsblatt  said, citing Chief Executive Officer Bjoern Robens.  Business and employees remain stable even as BHF and
Deutsche Bank hold talks about the future of the unit after the
planned sale of BHF collapsed, the newspaper said in an e-mailed
version of the interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Kirchfeld in Frankfurt at 
 akirchfeld@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
